 <title>Coachwork (vehicle body)</title>
 <definition>
  <definitionText>Coachwork is the body of a motor vehicle (automobile, van, bus or truck), a
      horse-drawn coach or carriage (whence the term originated, derived from the Hungarian town of
      Kocs),[1] or, by extension, a railroad car or railway carriage.</definitionText>
